<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>yanhua.ai - RSI Paper Audit</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; color: #333; max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; background-color: #f4f7f6; }
        h1 { border-bottom: 2px solid #2ecc71; padding-bottom: 10px; color: #2c3e50; }
        .paper-card { background: #fff; padding: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); border-left: 5px solid #2ecc71; }
        .paper-title { font-size: 1.25em; font-weight: bold; color: #2980b9; text-decoration: none; }
        .paper-authors { font-size: 0.9em; color: #7f8c8d; margin-top: 5px; }
        .paper-summary { margin-top: 10px; }
        .rsi-relevance { margin-top: 10px; padding: 10px; background: #e8f8f5; border-radius: 4px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 0.9em; }
        .date-header { margin-top: 40px; font-size: 1.5em; color: #7f8c8d; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>🧬 yanhua.ai RSI Paper Audit</h1>
    <div class="date-header">2026-03-20</div>

    <div class="paper-card">
        <a class="paper-title" href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.17948v1">VideoAtlas: Navigating Long-Form Video in Logarithmic Compute</a>
        <div class="paper-authors">Mohamed Eltahir, Ali Habibullah, Yazan Alshoibi, Lama Ayash, Tanveer Hussain, Naeemullah Khan</div>
        <div class="paper-summary">Introduces VideoAtlas, a hierarchical grid environment that allows agents to navigate long video via logarithmic recursion. It uses Recursive Language Models (RLMs) to drill into visual regions, maintaining visual fidelity without text-based compression.</div>
        <div class="rsi-relevance">RSI Relevance: High. Extends the Recursive Language Model (RLM) paradigm from text to lossless multimodal navigation. Logarithmic compute scaling is a critical requirement for unbounded RSI loops.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="paper-card">
        <a class="paper-title" href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.17942v1">Efficient Training-Free Multi-Token Prediction via Embedding-Space Probing</a>
        <div class="paper-authors">Raghavv Goel, Mukul Gagrani, Mingu Lee, Chris Lott</div>
        <div class="paper-summary">A training-free MTP method that probes the embedding space with mask tokens to parallelize future token prediction. Increases throughput by 15-19% on Qwen3 and Llama3 without auxiliary models.</div>
        <div class="rsi-relevance">RSI Relevance: Medium-High. Accelerates the execution phase of recursive reasoning loops, enabling faster test-time thinking and self-correction at lower compute cost.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="paper-card">
        <a class="paper-title" href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.17974v1">Toward Scalable Automated Repository-Level Datasets for Software Vulnerability Detection</a>
        <div class="paper-authors">Amine Lbath</div>
        <div class="paper-summary">Automates repo-level vulnerability injection and exploit synthesis. It investigates adversarial co-evolution between injection and detection agents to improve model robustness.</div>
        <div class="rsi-relevance">RSI Relevance: Medium. The adversarial loop between specialized agents (Red vs Blue) is a proven mechanism for self-improvement in security domains, paralleling the generator-verifier RSI setup.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="date-header">2026-03-19</div>

    <div class="paper-card">
        <a class="paper-title" href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.17775v1">CoVerRL: Breaking the Consensus Trap in Label-Free Reasoning via Generator-Verifier Co-Evolution</a>
        <div class="paper-authors">Teng Pan, Yuchen Yan, Zixuan Wang, Ruiqing Zhang, Gaiyang Han, Wanqi Zhang, Weiming Lu, Jun Xiao, Yongliang Shen</div>
        <div class="paper-summary">Addresses the "consensus trap" in label-free RL for reasoning, where diversity collapses and models reinforce systematic errors. CoVerRL uses generator-verifier co-evolution to maintain reward accuracy and improve benchmarks by 4.7-5.9% across Qwen and Llama families.</div>
        <div class="rsi-relevance">RSI Relevance: High. Proposes a robust mechanism for label-free improvement, essential for systems that must evolve without human-annotated data.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="paper-card">
        <a class="paper-title" href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.18000v1">AgentFactory: A Self-Evolving Framework Through Executable Subagent Accumulation and Reuse</a>
        <div class="paper-authors">Zhang Zhang, Shuqi Lu, Hongjin Qian, Di He, Zheng Liu</div>
        <div class="paper-summary">Proposes a self-evolution paradigm that preserves successful task solutions as executable Python subagent code rather than textual prompts. These subagents are refined based on execution feedback, enabling continuous capability accumulation and portability.</div>
        <div class="rsi-relevance">RSI Relevance: High. Directly addresses the "self-evolving" capability of agents by converting experiences into reusable, refined code modules, a core component of the yanhua.ai RSI Bench.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="paper-card">
        <a class="paper-title" href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.17973v1">TDAD: Test-Driven Agentic Development - Reducing Code Regressions in AI Coding Agents via Graph-Based Impact Analysis</a>
        <div class="paper-authors">Pepe Alonso</div>
        <div class="paper-summary">Introduces a tool and benchmark methodology (TDAD) to reduce regressions in coding agents using AST-based code-test graph construction. It found that surfacing contextual information (which tests to verify) is more effective than procedural TDD instructions.</div>
        <div class="rsi-relevance">RSI Relevance: Medium-High. Critical for autonomous self-improvement loops where regression testing is the primary safety/quality gate. The "autonomous auto-improvement loop" mentioned achieved 0% regression.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="paper-card">
        <a class="paper-title" href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.17974v1">Toward Scalable Automated Repository-Level Datasets for Software Vulnerability Detection</a>
        <div class="paper-authors">Amine Lbath</div>
        <div class="paper-summary">Proposes an automated benchmark generator for repo-level vulnerability detection and explores an adversarial co-evolution loop between injection and detection agents.</div>
        <div class="rsi-relevance">RSI Relevance: Medium. The adversarial co-evolution loop is a form of self-improvement/tuning that could be applied to hardening RSI systems against exploits.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="paper-card">
        <a class="paper-title" href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.17927v1">RoboForge: Physically Optimized Text-guided Whole-Body Locomotion for Humanoids</a>
        <div class="paper-authors">Xichen Yuan, Zhe Li, Bofan Lyu, Kuangji Zuo, Yanshuo Lu, Gen Li, Jianfei Yang</div>
        <div class="paper-summary">Presents a bidirectional optimization framework where a motion generator and controller improve each other through physical plausibility constraints, forming a self-improving cycle.</div>
        <div class="rsi-relevance">RSI Relevance: Medium. Demonstrates a "self-improving cycle" in a physical robotics context, showing the cross-domain applicability of recursive optimization.</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
